Global EEG and ECG Electrode Market Insights
EEG and ECG Electrode Market size was valued at USD 6.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 10.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.1% from 2024 to 2030.

EEG and ECG Electrode Market Overview
The EEG and ECG electrode market was valued at USD 2.5 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030. This growth is driven by the increasing adoption of electroencephalography (EEG) and electrocardiography (ECG) devices for the diagnosis of neurological and cardiovascular diseases, respectively. Additionally, technological advancements and the rising demand for wearable medical devices are further fueling market expansion. The growing awareness regarding early disease detection and the increasing number of patients with chronic conditions are some of the key factors contributing to the market's growth.

